column67: Do you have any comments about which features in the images you find appealing?
The ones that are clear and look the most natural to me are more appealing.
Vibrant in colour, strong contrasts, close up, full of life

I very much went off of color first, composition second. I noticed that the oversaturated pictures seems over-edited, and thereby taking away the realism of the photo - making me dislike it. Parallel to this, big color contrast seen in for instance in the sunset pictures looked a bit “overdone” and commercial almost. Like generic apple/windows wallpaper - and for this reason I was not drawn to these pictures either. 
The more subdued tones were more pleasant for the eye, and seemed more realistic (but I realize that I might possible be impacted by the current minimalistic design trends, and the love for the neutral palette that’s very “up in the times”) 
As for the mountains and peaks in some of the pictures, I noticed to be more drawn to taller mountains - for more depth and a more interesting composition.
Colors and clearity of the motive (no clouds in front for example)

The Sunsets are undeniably appealing and hold a special place in my heart. There is a captivating beauty in watching the sun slowly descend below the horizon, painting the sky with an array of warm and vibrant colors. Overall, the appeal of sunsets lies in their ability to awaken my/our senses, inspire contemplation, and remind me of the beauty and transience of life.
